{"priority": "major", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{e799e7f6-0caa-464a-97f8-8605a37ebfb1}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-legacy", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-legacy", "uuid": "{e799e7f6-0caa-464a-97f8-8605a37ebfb1}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/135/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/135.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/135/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/135/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/135/explicit-load-of-ixgbe-module-needs-to"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/135/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "title": "Explicit load of ixgbe module needs to escape call to `uname`", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 1, "content": {"raw": "When we [add the call to insmod](#!/osrf/cloudsim/src/dd27bedea0f59e94fc40bb571a0b9c2743c63046/cloudsimd/launchers/vrc_contest.py?at=default#cl-698) in `/etc/rc.local`, we need to escape the backquote characters, so that they appear literally in `/etc/rc.local`.  Otherwise, substitution happens when that file is created, resulting in a kernel version-specific path.  Then the module won't load properly if booted into a different kernel.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>When we <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/cloudsim/src/dd27bedea0f59e94fc40bb571a0b9c2743c63046/cloudsimd/launchers/vrc_contest.py?at=default#cl-698\" rel=\"nofollow\">add the call to insmod</a> in <code>/etc/rc.local</code>, we need to escape the backquote characters, so that they appear literally in <code>/etc/rc.local</code>.  Otherwise, substitution happens when that file is created, resulting in a kernel version-specific path.  Then the module won't load properly if booted into a different kernel.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-06-04T20:29:05.561527+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2013-06-08T01:32:05.923895+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 135}